      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Each solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via benchmark problems with known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Ansys and the FDA in-house code were verified against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 and LE10 for linear elasticity. DePuy Synthes solver verified against cantilever beam and thick-walled cylinder benchmarks. All errors within 1% of analytical solutions. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 5% between successive refinements; GCI < 2%.",
      "rationale": "Systematic h-refinement study conducted with three mesh densities (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~520k, fine ~1.4M). GCI for stiffness QoI: 0.9%. QoI change between medium and fine: 1.4%. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must converge below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error less than 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with displacement convergence criterion 1e-6. Energy balance monitored at each increment; maximum imbalance 0.04%. No divergence or cutback events recorded across 11-specimen ensemble. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup and execution must follow documented SOPs; independent reviewer must confirm boundary conditions, material assignments, and load application prior to result extraction.",
      "rationale": "Model setup SOPs documented and version-controlled. Independent reviewer (second analyst) verified boundary conditions, contact definitions, material property assignments, and load application for all three solver implementations before result extraction. Discrepancies resolved via documented review log. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection must be justified by material characterization data; contact formulation must be appropriate for the screw-rod interface kinematics.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as bilinear isotropic hardening; material parameters derived from tensile coupon tests (n=6) on same lot material. UHMWPE blocks modeled as linear elastic with published modulus; sensitivity study confirms QoI insensitivity to ±15% modulus variation. Penalty contact with augmented Lagrange stabilization used for screw-rod interface; frictionless and frictional (μ=0.2) variants compared; difference in stiffness QoI < 2%. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs must be traceable to measured or published sources; parametric uncertainty analysis must bound QoI sensitivity to input variation.",
      "rationale": "Geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of three production screws (mean ± 1 SD used). Material properties from coupon tests. Torque preload on set screw estimated from torque-angle calibration curve; sensitivity to ±10% torque variation assessed — stiffness QoI changes 1.8%, yield force 2.3%. All inputs documented in model input log. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be production-representative; lot traceability and dimensional inspection records must be available.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-lot non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and 5.5 mm titanium rods. Lot certificates of conformance available. Dimensional inspection of 3 specimens per lot confirmed geometry within engineering drawing tolerances. Specimens distributed across two independent test laboratories. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate COU loading environment; at minimum two independent load configurations or laboratories must be represented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed strictly per ASTM F1717 protocol at a single compression-bending load angle (10°) and single crosshead rate (25 mm/min). Both laboratories used identical protocol. Only one test condition was exercised; alternative load angles or rates were not explored. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3 — identified as a known gap. Compensating evidence: three QoIs extracted from the single condition provide partial coverage. This shortfall is acknowledged in the decision record.",
      "gap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Equivalency of input parameters between the simulation and the physical test must be formally evaluated, including torque preload, boundary fixture stiffness, and alignment tolerances.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that because the ASTM F1717 protocol prescribes fixture geometry and loading alignment with high specificity, the equivalency of input parameters between simulation and test is considered self-evident and therefore not applicable to this COU. Accordingly, no formal equivalency mapping exercise was performed and no equivalency evidence package was assembled. The factor was not scored against the V&V 40 gradation table. Note: the correct encoding for a factor determined to be inapplicable is 'not-applicable'; the use of 'not-assessed' here reflects an administrative omission rather than a deliberate scoping decision, and no requiredLevel or achievedLevel has been established for this factor despite the elevated model risk level of 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) must be computed for each QoI; metric must account for both experimental and simulation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for all three QoIs per ASME V&V 40 Section 9. Experimental uncertainty estimated from inter-specimen and inter-laboratory variability (pooled SD). Simulation uncertainty estimated via GCI and input sensitivity. E/uval values: stiffness 1.41, yield force 0.87, force at 40 mm 1.62 — all below 1.96 threshold. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to the clinical failure mode and to the regulatory submission acceptance criteria.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary metrics cited in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to construct mechanical integrity under physiological bending. Clinical relevance: construct stiffness relates to load sharing; yield force relates to permanent deformation risk; force at 40 mm relates to catastrophic failure threshold. All three are cited in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. Required level 2 exceeded; achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted under conditions sufficiently similar to the COU that extrapolation risk is low; any differences must be bounded by sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation specimens are identical in design and lot to the device under review. Test protocol (ASTM F1717) is the same standard referenced in the COU. Two independent laboratories provide cross-validation. The only extrapolation is from bench to in vivo loading environment, which is addressed by the conservative F1717 load levels (exceeding physiological estimates by factor of ~2). Sensitivity analysis confirms QoI rank-ordering is preserved across the extrapolation. Required level 3 achieved."
    }
